This paper deals with privacy-preserving data aggregation, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the complexity of the protocols proposed, which suggests that it could be categorized under computer science and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper deals with data management and privacy, which could place it under the categories of databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses communication and computation complexity, which could place it under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
